Fixes #1084 

Although it is CLEARLY insinuated in the `ArrayParameter` docstring that an `ArrayParameter` must return a numpy array, some `ArrayParameter` subclasses apparently return lists or tuples. Since there is no good reason *not* to accept such an input, this PR makes the measurement context manager do just that.

Changes proposed in this pull request:
- Handle any type of input in `add_result`, allowing for lists and tuples

@spauka, I probably missed some corner case, so I'd be happy to have your eyes on this.

@QCoDeS/core
